title: Arul Beyond the Obvious: Apprehension, Causation and Emergence
description:
Causation and Emergence
Underneath all math, science and physics is the presumption that we are beings who can apprehend it.  How did that come to be?
Albert Einstein:  "Perfection of means and confusion of goals, in my opinion, seem to characterize the age."
Scientists are not philosophically trained, trying to take over ethics without enough familiarity of he philosophy of ethics.
Emergence - it's real, but we have no idea what it really means, how it comes to be and how it is existentially real.
Physical, Logical and Mental Causation



Sharon Glotzer on particle physics:  https://youtu.be/et5KcmdCXRk
Dr. James Tour:  https://youtu.be/zU7Lww-sBPg
George F. R. Ellis on Purpose:  https://youtu.be/FpfCDIhOxrE
George F. R. Ellis on the Moral Question:  https://youtu.be/fKObfyXIIg8
